Class FixedObjectOutputStream

java.lang.Object
java.io.OutputStream
java.io.ObjectOutputStream
org.example.acrastt.utils.FixedObjectOutputStream
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable, DataOutput, Flushable, ObjectOutput, ObjectStreamConstants, AutoCloseable
public class FixedObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream
A fixed object writer than does not throw StreamCorruptedException when writing multiple Objects.

  • Method Details

    • fixedWriteObject

      public static void fixedWriteObject (Object o, String file)
      Write Object in a fixed format. If the file is empty, header will be written. Otherwise, no header will be written.
      Parameters:
      o - the object to write
      file - the name of the file to write to

    • getFixedObjectOutputStream

      public static ObjectOutputStream getFixedObjectOutputStream (String file)
      Get a fixed object output stream. If the file is empty, it will create an ObjectOutputStream that writes headers. Otherwise, it will create an ObjectOutputStream that doesn't write headers. Only writing one object per ObjectOutputStream will be recommended.
      Parameters:
      file - the name of the file to write to
      Returns:
      the fixed object output stream
